div.p: This shows a simple memory configuration with parallel memory chips. Each chip is selected by the upper address bits, thus forming "banks" in memory space.
The specific implementation is up to the wiring and programmer to account for the memory topography. As long as the latches and banks conform to the timing requirements, it will work.
